simulation.simulation

Class SimulationConductor

  • java.lang.Object
    • simulation.simulation.SimulationConductor

  • public class SimulationConductor
extends java.lang.Object
    A class for conducting a simulation with given parameters multiple number of times so that its results can be averaged.

    A SimulationConductor object gathers averaged statistics for the set of simulations conducted by it. They are accessible with appropriate getters. Statistic are gathered for each language in the pattern simulation of a conductor. A SimulationConductor holds pointers to languages in an array, and therefore each language can be identified with an id (index in the array).

    See Also:
    Simulation, Language, SimulationConductorSerializer

    • Method Detail

      • conduct

        public void conduct(int stopIteration)
        Conducts this conductor's patternSimulation until the simulation's population reaches lexicon identity or stopIteration are conducted. During the conductment, statistics are gathered and at the end, they are merged to averaged statistics held by this conductor.
        Parameters:
        stopIteration - maximal number of iterations for this conductment

      • conduct

        public void conduct(int times,
                    int stopIteration)
        Conducts this conductor's patternSimulation multiple times. It is equivalent to invoking this.conduct(stopIteration times times.
        Parameters:
        times - number of times to conduct the patternSimulation
        stopIteration - maximal number of iterations for this conductment
